1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,320
You avoided me
because you're afraid of your own heart.

2
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:46,320
-Afraid of what?
-Afraid of falling in love with me, right?

3
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:48,800
But I was so damn happy

4
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:50,560
that he finally died.

5
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,800
You really think we can be just friends?

6
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:56,800
I guess.

7
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:00,640
I want to compete
with Rachen fair and square.

8
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:03,200
Let the results speak
and let us prove our capabilities.

9
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,800
You already took Dad's leftovers.

10
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:07,520
So get ready to take mine next, Trai.

11
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:09,640
How the hell can you say that?!

12
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:10,640
How can you say that?!

13
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:11,880
How can you say that?!

14
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,640
-Fine dining or BBQ?
-BBQ

15
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:15,080
-Mall or market?
-Market.

16
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,960
-Gambling or working?
-Working.

17
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:18,520
-Mr. Rachen or Trai?
-Trai.

18
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:24,360
But I won't throw money at you
like Rachen does.

19
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:27,000
Then what will you throw at me?
Don't tell me…

20
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,440
Your body?

21
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,320
No.

22
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,200
Kanah.

23
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:35,840
What are you making?

24
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:38,880
It smells so good…

25
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:46,560
What? What should I do?

26
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:54,080
Mr. Trai.

27
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:55,960
Why are you here so early?

28
00:03:56,040 --> 00:04:00,040
I thought you might miss me,
so I came to see you before going to work.

29
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,480
Come on, let's eat. It's done.

30
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,040
This looks like a hotel breakfast.

31
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,680
Hey.

32
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,440
This is free, right?

33
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:30,800
Weren't you the one who told me
nothing's free in this world?

34
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:35,440
The coffee is in exchange
for the soy milk you bought me that day.

35
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,440
The bread

36
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:39,680
is for the fried dough sticks.

37
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:42,680
And the rest…

38
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,440
is just for me to see your smile.

39
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,720
-Smile?
-Yeah.

40
00:04:57,240 --> 00:05:00,680
You have to smile at me
every morning, afternoon, evening.

41
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:02,280
All day, all night,

42
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,440
all month, and forever.

43
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,920
Then…

44
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:18,040
why don't you take out your phone
and take a photo of me right now?

45
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,080
So you can see me

46
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:24,840
smiling all day, all month, all year.
Stick it on the wall at your house.

47
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:33,000
Go on, take it.

48
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:38,800
Why are you staring?
Take out your phone and take it already.

49
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:40,960
When you blush,

50
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:43,960
you're a million times cuter.

51
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:57,920
I'm eating this.

52
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:30,280
Mr. Trai. Oh.

53
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,520
I'm sorry. I didn't know that you were--

54
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:58,960
Say what you have to say.
And if it's not important…

55
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:06,280
Mr. Chan, Mr. Tritot's investigator,
has contacted us.

56
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,560
Mr. Chan was on another case,
so he cut off communication.

57
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:17,320
When he found out
Mr. Tritot passed away, he contacted us.

58
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:20,120
He wanted to speak to you personally.

59
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:22,120
He wasn't confident about his safety.

60
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:25,920
His place in Bangkok was searched.

61
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,520
His computer and phone

62
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,080
were infected with viruses.

63
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:32,240
All the data he previously sent
to Mr. Tritot is gone.

64
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,760
Just like what happened
to Dad's equipment.

65
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:37,400
Mr. Trai, Mr. Chan is sitting over there.

66
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,720
-Mr. Chan, hello.
-Oh, Mr. Trai.

67
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,560
Hello. Please have a seat.

68
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:47,120
Mr. Trai.

69
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:50,640
I'm very sorry about your father.
I just heard about it.

70
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:54,040
Thank you. You know who did it, right?

71
00:07:57,720 --> 00:08:00,360
The perpetrator is extremely professional.

72
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:04,200
They left no traces at all.

73
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:07,400
But I traced CCTV footage.

74
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:10,800
Luckily, I found a car dashcam.

75
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,520
When I reviewed it,

76
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:19,240
I saw a suspect riding a motorcycle away.

77
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:21,160
Let's get straight to it.
Who is the culprit?

78
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:30,200
I backed everything up onto a hard drive.

79
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:32,680
You can check it later.

80
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:37,680
-Hey!
-Mr. Chan!

81
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,680
Mr. Chan! Mr. Chan!

82
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:40,680
Mr. Chan!

83
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,800
Prarop, call 1669.

84
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:43,920
Yes, sir.

85
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:45,840
Mr. Chan.

86
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,400
There's a man in his thirties.

87
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:49,120
He collapsed and is unconscious.

88
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:51,320
-Mr. Trai!
-Yes.

89
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,560
Pakbung! Pakbung.

90
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:24,280
You almost died!

91
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:41,360
-This way, please.
-Mr. Trai.

92
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:45,200
-Excuse me.
-Alright.

93
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:51,720
How's Mr. Chan?

94
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:54,040
They couldn't save him.

95
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,320
They're preparing the body
for autopsy now.

96
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:04,760
Mr. Trai, we got the CCTV footage.

97
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,840
Excuse me, this is my coffee.

98
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:31,560
The police suspect it was poison.

99
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,880
How many more people have to die?!

100
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,520
-Mr. Trai!
-Calm down.

101
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:39,680
Hey.

102
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:40,680
-Hey.
-Mr. Trai.

103
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:42,360
Mr. Trai, please. No!

104
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,360
Please calm down.

105
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:50,240
Calm down.

106
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:55,200
Sit down first.

107
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:56,840
Please. Slowly.

108
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:08,720
At least, we got the hard drive.

109
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:14,280
But it's broken.

110
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:17,920
Even so, data can still be recovered.
Better than letting him have it.

111
00:12:18,520 --> 00:12:20,480
I should've grabbed it.

112
00:12:21,160 --> 00:12:23,320
I was right there.

113
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:25,240
Pakbung.

114
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:28,200
This has nothing to do with you.

115
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:30,280
I don't want you to risk your life.

116
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:33,600
Didn't you see? Someone died.
You almost died too.

117
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,240
I'm sorry.

118
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:43,120
I just wanted to help.

119
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:46,080
I really want to keep you out of this.

120
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:49,920
I don't want you involved
or knowing anything at all.

121
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:53,320
But when I saw you there,

122
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,280
I was so damn happy.

123
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:01,560
Thank you.

124
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,040
Thank you for helping me.

125
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,440
I…

126
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:13,960
But don't do it next time.

127
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,280
Then why did you talk so loudly
that I could hear?

128
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,200
Oh, right.

129
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:30,080
How did the culprit
know your movements anyway?

130
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:35,760
I was the only one
listening in on your conversation.

131
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:41,640
Wait, Prarop,

132
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:46,440
didn't you say both Mr. Chan's computer
and phone were infected?

133
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:47,360
Yes.

134
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:51,040
But if Mr. Chan was out of town, how could
the culprit have installed a virus?

135
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:53,040
You don't need to do it in person now.

136
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:55,480
Viruses can be sent via spyware

137
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,320
using links and such.

138
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,360
Scammers use this all the time.

139
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:01,480
Oh,

140
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:03,760
I've seen this on the news.

141
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:08,400
The scams that drain people's money
use this method too.

142
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:11,760
They trick people into opening bank apps,

143
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:15,440
using messages and links as bait.

144
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:17,000
Links to click?

145
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:18,720
Yes.

146
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:19,800
Like this?

147
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,080
Hey, Lee.

148
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:35,680
-What?
-Why are there 2 links to the Be Rich app?

149
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:39,360
Hey. Since when?

150
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:51,240
That means one of them is fake.

151
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:53,560
Lee, you've been bugged.

152
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:54,560
Yes…

153
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:55,560
-Really?
-Yes!

154
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:58,160
It's fine. I'll delete it. I'll handle it.

155
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:11,720
So you finally figured it out, Trai.

156
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:18,840
And you, Pakbung,

157
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:22,000
you shouldn't have
stuck your nose into this.

158
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,720
You're done for.

159
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,280
MR. RACHEN

160
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:04,560
Yes, Mr. Rachen.

161
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:08,960
Yes. Understood.

162
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:11,760
I'll hurry over.

163
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:35,680
Are you suspecting my man?

164
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:46,080
Be careful.

165
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:47,520
-Is it good?
-A bit to the left.

166
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,440
-Huh? Left?
-This way.

167
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:50,880
-To the left?
-Yes.

168
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:52,240
Wait.

169
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:53,160
This way.

170
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:54,480
What is all this?

171
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:57,960
You and Mr. Trai are in danger.

172
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:00,200
So we have to build
a fortress to protect you

173
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:02,360
in case the culprit
breaks in to attack again.

174
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:05,080
And if someone breaks in,

175
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:07,560
these CCTV cameras
will send an alert immediately.

176
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:09,400
Pakbung,

177
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:11,600
I know

178
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:14,680
you're shocked
and scared out of your mind.

179
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,040
But it's fine.

180
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:20,160
All of us are here with you.

181
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:25,200
And all of us are going to protect you.

182
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,480
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

183
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:32,920
So you're sleeping at my place too?

184
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,240
Well, yes.

185
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:37,600
The culprit saw you helping me.

186
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:39,880
You might be the next target.

187
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:42,360
How could I leave you alone?
It's dangerous.

188
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:46,520
Let me stay and take care of you.

189
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:51,840
Why don't you try
taking care of yourself first?

190
00:17:57,840 --> 00:17:58,680
Exactly.

191
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:01,520
Trai needs to be taken care of.

192
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:02,600
Right?

193
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:05,280
If we let Trai wander around out there,

194
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:06,880
he'll be in danger.

195
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:09,800
What if one day the culprit comes back

196
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:12,680
with a knife and stabs him
in the stomach like this?

197
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:15,680
What will we do then?

198
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:18,080
-You have to take care of Trai.
-Yeah.

199
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:19,200
He's injured too.

200
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:20,320
-Yes.
-He's hurt.

201
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,880
-It really hurts.
-Ow, it hurts.

202
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:24,360
-It hurts, it really hurts.
-Look.

203
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,560
Ow, it hurts.

204
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:28,360
-Mr. Trai.
-Hey, hey.

205
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:30,800
-What?
-He's acting.

206
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,080
Okay, okay.

207
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:34,440
Sleep here then.

208
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:37,120
I'm not kicking you out or anything.

209
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:43,680
Let's all sleep here. 500 baht per person.

210
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:46,840
Niuniu, one. Samlee, two.

211
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:50,040
Lee, three. Prarop, four.

212
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:51,360
You, five.

213
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:55,360
That's 2,500 total.

214
00:18:57,120 --> 00:18:58,120
Cheapskate.

215
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:01,920
Help pay for the water and electricity.

216
00:19:28,120 --> 00:19:29,720
Is everything ready?

217
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:32,920
Yes.

218
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:36,960
Just "yes"? That's a bit short, isn't it?

219
00:19:37,520 --> 00:19:38,400
Mika.

220
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:42,000
Rachen's not respecting you.

221
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:44,800
Actually,

222
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:48,480
he's crossed you so many times already,

223
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:51,000
like when hiring that company.

224
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:53,560
Who you hire is your right.

225
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:55,880
But don't let there be any problems.

226
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,240
Yes.

227
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:04,840
So is that the only word you can say?

228
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:11,240
Ms. Mika,

229
00:20:11,320 --> 00:20:14,800
the chef came to cook steak for you.
It's really delicious.

230
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:15,920
Please try some.

231
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:22,280
Excuse me.

232
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:24,920
Mr. Rachen, the app has a problem.

233
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:29,120
Excuse me.
I need to handle this right now.

234
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:45,680
Why won't he let me go?
He's haunting me even in my dreams.

235
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,680
Why don't you
dedicate merit to Mr. Tritot?

236
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:50,440
Maybe you'll feel more at peace.

237
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:53,760
Why would I do that
for someone who hated me?

238
00:20:54,840 --> 00:20:56,560
Even if I dedicate merit to him,
he probably wouldn't accept it.

239
00:20:59,320 --> 00:21:00,480
If you think about it,

240
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:04,160
Mr. Tritot had his reasons to hate you.

241
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:13,120
Crying again?

242
00:21:16,960 --> 00:21:19,440
Since you married me,
you've cried every single day.

243
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:23,800
Tell me.
What do you even gain from crying?

244
00:21:25,840 --> 00:21:29,520
Or is squeezing out tears
the only thing you're good at?

245
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:37,200
And who is it that made me like this?

246
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:38,120
Who?

247
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,440
-It's you.
-It's you people.

248
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:45,320
You deceived me. And Trai ruined my life.

249
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:48,720
Stop making things up. Weren't you the one

250
00:21:49,520 --> 00:21:51,520
who dragged Trai
into taking responsibility?

251
00:21:52,240 --> 00:21:53,520
Don't think I didn't know.

252
00:21:54,120 --> 00:21:58,120
You intended to hold that press conference
and lie that Trai was the one driving.

253
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:02,080
-You knew?
-Yes.

254
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,760
I knew. I saw through you.

255
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:06,960
That's why I sent people
to stop it in time.

256
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:09,760
Otherwise, you would've
completely framed my son.

257
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:12,240
I didn't frame him.

258
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:15,520
Trai's the one at fault.
He forced me to drink!

259
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:16,920
Maybe just the first glass!

260
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:20,560
Swear that you didn't drink
the next ones by your own choice.

261
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:22,840
Can you swear?

262
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:29,240
Trai loved you.

263
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:32,160
He gave up everything,

264
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:35,920
sacrificed himself,
to take responsibility for you.

265
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:40,280
And you? You say you love him,

266
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:44,720
yet you don't hesitate
to hurt him, to betray him.

267
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:49,480
A woman like you can't be trusted.

268
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:54,520
I'll never let you return
to my son's life again.

269
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:59,200
He hated me. Can't I hate him too?

270
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:03,560
I won't stay rotting
in the hole he buried me in.

271
00:23:04,360 --> 00:23:05,440
Da.

272
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:08,920
Everything I lost,

273
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,280
I'm going to take it all back, Mom.

274
00:23:35,440 --> 00:23:36,720
Can't sleep?

275
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:40,920
I'm here to see my dad.

276
00:23:42,720 --> 00:23:44,680
Do you think my dad has found my mom yet?

277
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:47,400
He probably has.

278
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:49,160
That star

279
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:51,440
and that star…

280
00:23:53,280 --> 00:23:55,280
are probably your parents.

281
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:02,160
Hello, Mr. Tritot, Mrs. Duangdao.

282
00:24:03,360 --> 00:24:05,000
Are you doing well?

283
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:07,560
Can you see me and Mr. Trai?

284
00:24:09,560 --> 00:24:10,680
Today,

285
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:14,800
Mr. Trai almost died.

286
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:21,240
Please protect him too.

287
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:30,600
Did I greet the wrong stars?

288
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:34,240
You're the one
who almost got hit by a car.

289
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:42,720
Back then, I was really scared.

290
00:24:43,840 --> 00:24:45,560
When that car came rushing toward me,

291
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:47,680
I thought,

292
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:51,040
"That's it! I'm dead!"

293
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:54,440
"Yama's coming to pick me up for sure."

294
00:24:56,920 --> 00:24:58,000
I was scared too.

295
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:01,040
I was scared you'd leave
and go be with my parents.

296
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:04,120
I'm not running off anywhere anytime soon.

297
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:07,720
There are still so many things
I haven't done yet.

298
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:09,680
Like what?

299
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:15,960
To stop running

300
00:25:17,120 --> 00:25:18,600
and admit how I feel.

301
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:22,800
Also,

302
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:26,520
your dad didn't exactly adore me either.

303
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:30,160
If I ran off right away,

304
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:33,600
your dad would definitely scold me
for leaving you behind.

305
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:42,720
Pakbung.

306
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:48,200
Can you promise me?

307
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:56,400
Of course. I promise I won't leave you.

308
00:25:56,480 --> 00:25:57,960
No, not that.

309
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:00,640
Promise you won't get involved in this.

310
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:04,440
Once the Be Rich app launch event is over,

311
00:26:04,520 --> 00:26:06,280
don't take any work
related to Be Rich again.

312
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:14,480
You are Be Rich.

313
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:22,480
So are you banning me
from being involved with you too?

314
00:26:33,880 --> 00:26:35,680
If you being close to me…

315
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:41,440
means you'll have to risk
your life again like today, then I--

316
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:47,520
Are you going to push me away?

317
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:07,640
Mr. Rachen, I think that's enough.

318
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:08,720
Shut up, Rut.

319
00:28:09,840 --> 00:28:12,920
You know what? Every time

320
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:15,600
I give everything to someone,

321
00:28:16,280 --> 00:28:17,520
Trai shows up

322
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:19,680
and steals what's mine.

323
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:21,920
He takes what's mine!

324
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,760
What the hell!

325
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:26,280
Why does he have to take
my happiness away?!

326
00:28:26,360 --> 00:28:29,440
Can he not stand seeing me happy or what?

327
00:28:31,160 --> 00:28:33,080
Why is he even in this world?
(Watch on www.kisskh.la to support Admin)

328
00:28:34,520 --> 00:28:35,720
Exactly.

329
00:28:37,760 --> 00:28:39,120
If Mr. Trai is still around,

330
00:28:40,080 --> 00:28:41,600
you might end up with nothing at all.

331
00:28:44,640 --> 00:28:45,880
You're right.

332
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:48,400
So why don't you try it, then?

333
00:28:50,560 --> 00:28:52,480
-Try what?
-Well…

334
00:28:53,040 --> 00:28:54,960
Try making Mr. Trai
disappear from this world.

335
00:29:03,760 --> 00:29:05,200
Are you insane, Rut?

336
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:09,880
He's my brother.
How the hell could I do that?

337
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:13,560
Do you want to lose everything,
especially the person you love,

338
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:15,640
to Mr. Trai again?

339
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:18,720
You can win. You can be number one.

340
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:21,960
But even easier than that,
you don't have to compete

341
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:24,600
if Mr. Trai is gone from this world.

342
00:29:41,320 --> 00:29:42,760
The world without Trai, huh?

343
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:52,400
Ugh, when are you gonna tell me?

344
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:54,640
What do you have with Mr. Trai?

345
00:29:54,720 --> 00:29:56,200
I slept right next to you all night.

346
00:29:56,280 --> 00:29:57,560
So?

347
00:29:58,480 --> 00:30:02,160
And if you ever get married,
throw the bouquet to me, okay?

348
00:30:02,240 --> 00:30:03,800
Me too.

349
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:05,680
You two are already thinking way too far.

350
00:30:05,760 --> 00:30:07,480
Come back to reality first.

351
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:10,880
We've got the culprit situation,
we've got work.

352
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:13,840
There are like ten million
unresolved problems.

353
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:15,880
Let's fix at least one thing first,

354
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:17,920
then I'll think about that.

355
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:22,720
Stuff like that doesn't need
to be thought out.

356
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:25,160
It's all heart. Pure heart.

357
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:29,200
-Aw.
-My heart's fluttering.

358
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:32,680
-Look at you.
-You're blushing.

359
00:30:32,760 --> 00:30:34,760
-You're hiding your smile.
-Yeah.

360
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:36,120
Mr. Rachen.

361
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:48,280
I didn't abandon the job, okay?

362
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:52,200
But the structures can only
be installed after the mall closes.

363
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:54,680
That's when we can go in
and set everything up for you.

364
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:57,040
I'm not blaming you for anything.

365
00:30:58,720 --> 00:31:01,640
Then why are you here?
I thought you're upset about the job.

366
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:04,120
I'm here so I can take you
to the job tonight.

367
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:09,160
So you can work with me all night, right?

368
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:14,240
-Rut.
-Yes.

369
00:31:14,320 --> 00:31:16,520
Book a hotel nearby the work site.

370
00:31:16,600 --> 00:31:17,920
Yes, sir.

371
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:22,240
Tonight, you have to sleep with me.

372
00:31:30,360 --> 00:31:33,600
I finished everything for today, but…

373
00:31:33,680 --> 00:31:36,360
this wasn't part of the deal we agreed on.

374
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:37,960
Then how much more do you want?

375
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:43,040
Or do you want me to cancel the jobs
I hired Petch's agency for?

376
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:52,160
You're a public figure, Mr. Rachen.

377
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:55,000
You're handsome, you're rich.

378
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:58,360
Whatever you're doing, think it through.

379
00:31:59,600 --> 00:32:01,360
And what do you think I'm gonna do to you?

380
00:32:02,560 --> 00:32:04,840
You don't want people
to see you in a negative light.

381
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:07,320
I'm trying not to think badly of you.

382
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:09,280
I just want to be with you.

383
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:15,480
What? Rachen took a woman to a hotel?

384
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:17,560
Send me the picture.

385
00:32:23,960 --> 00:32:25,640
Pakbung.

386
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:29,080
Pakbung!

387
00:32:32,840 --> 00:32:33,760
Mika!

388
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:36,720
Mom.

389
00:32:36,800 --> 00:32:39,160
Rachen took that Pakbung into a hotel.

390
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:41,000
Look.

391
00:32:41,520 --> 00:32:43,360
It's my friend's hotel too.

392
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:45,680
She did it on purpose to challenge me.

393
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:50,440
How could Rachen do this to me?

394
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:55,360
I can't take it anymore.
I'm going to kill her!

395
00:32:56,320 --> 00:32:59,080
I don't want you becoming
a murderer because of a man.

396
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:03,240
So what? Are you going
to order me to use my brain again?

397
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:06,920
No! I can't think. I don't want to think.

398
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:09,680
I want to slap her. Did you hear me?
I want to slap her.

399
00:33:09,760 --> 00:33:11,160
-Slap her. Slap her.
-Mika!

400
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:12,800
-Mika!
-Slap--

401
00:33:14,080 --> 00:33:15,240
Snap out of it!

402
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:21,240
Mom…

403
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:34,240
Oh, Mr. Rachen.

404
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:37,080
Samlee just texted me.

405
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:39,800
The technicians forgot to put
the Be Rich logo on the stage.

406
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:42,160
I think I need to hurry back.

407
00:33:42,840 --> 00:33:43,840
Pakbung, you're here?

408
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:46,240
-Hey!
-Hey!

409
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:48,600
Mr. Rachen is so nice!

410
00:33:48,680 --> 00:33:50,400
He booked us the room
so we can sleep here.

411
00:33:51,120 --> 00:33:52,240
Come take a look.

412
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:53,560
Yes. Come in.

413
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:55,720
-Come in. Follow me.
-Come in.

414
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:57,560
-The bed is so soft.
-So soft!

415
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:02,680
I thought you weren't
thinking badly of me.

416
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:12,640
I'm sorry.

417
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:15,600
Does it hurt? Look, you're all red.

418
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:18,000
Mom…

419
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,440
You don't love me.

420
00:34:21,520 --> 00:34:23,440
Of course I love you.

421
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:29,240
I love you so much.

422
00:34:30,160 --> 00:34:32,680
That's why I tried
to bring you back to your senses.

423
00:34:33,360 --> 00:34:35,640
You can hate anyone you want,

424
00:34:37,760 --> 00:34:41,280
but don't ever get yourself
into trouble. Understand?

425
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:47,560
I can't think. I don't know
what I'm supposed to do.

426
00:34:48,360 --> 00:34:50,400
I have a hint for you.

427
00:34:51,040 --> 00:34:51,880
Want to hear it?

428
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:59,600
If that little girl

429
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:02,800
messes with someone
who belongs to you and you don't like it,

430
00:35:02,880 --> 00:35:05,600
then use her people to your advantage.

431
00:35:07,880 --> 00:35:09,040
Her people?

432
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:17,320
Tomorrow, call Tong. Tell him to come here
and trim the hedges.

433
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:18,360
Make them even.

434
00:35:18,440 --> 00:35:19,560
Her father.

435
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:40,560
I'm sorry, Mr. Rachen.

436
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:45,160
I misunderstood your intentions a bit.

437
00:35:47,280 --> 00:35:48,360
It's fine.

438
00:35:50,360 --> 00:35:52,080
I also spoke too vaguely.

439
00:35:54,040 --> 00:35:55,840
I just wanted to see

440
00:35:57,640 --> 00:36:00,440
how far you'd be willing to follow me.

441
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:05,160
Standing outside the room like this
is already pretty far, you know.

442
00:36:06,360 --> 00:36:08,160
But if it were Trai, you'd go inside.

443
00:36:08,240 --> 00:36:12,440
Even if it were Mr. Trai,
I wouldn't go in.

444
00:36:14,320 --> 00:36:16,000
If I had a choice,

445
00:36:16,520 --> 00:36:19,000
I wouldn't follow any man into a room.

446
00:36:19,080 --> 00:36:20,840
I'd be the one to open the door

447
00:36:21,720 --> 00:36:24,800
and choose the person I liked to come in.

448
00:36:28,200 --> 00:36:30,040
So is there anyone you like right now?

449
00:36:30,120 --> 00:36:33,360
I don't even have the money to book

450
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:35,000
a luxury hotel room like this.

451
00:36:35,520 --> 00:36:38,040
Why would I exhaust myself
thinking about liking someone?

452
00:36:39,160 --> 00:36:40,960
Then when you're ready someday,

453
00:36:41,880 --> 00:36:43,880
if I ask you as a man

454
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:45,920
to not choose Trai,

455
00:36:48,160 --> 00:36:49,840
would you do it?

456
00:36:56,800 --> 00:37:00,280
I can't guarantee the future.

457
00:37:01,840 --> 00:37:04,720
Then if I order you as your boss

458
00:37:05,680 --> 00:37:07,360
while we're working together…

459
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:10,360
that you must not choose Trai,

460
00:37:13,640 --> 00:37:15,040
can you do it?

461
00:37:21,320 --> 00:37:22,240
Can you?

462
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:01,840
It's about to start,
and not even ten people are here.

463
00:38:02,480 --> 00:38:05,960
On Mr. Rachen's side, they're
giving away gold, giving away motorcycles,

464
00:38:06,040 --> 00:38:07,800
so people signed up over there instead.

465
00:38:09,760 --> 00:38:12,960
So they only care
if you dangle prizes in front of them?

466
00:38:14,760 --> 00:38:18,160
Did you forget sincerity
can make people interested too?

467
00:38:22,160 --> 00:38:25,400
Actually, a lot of people want to come,
but they're stuck at work.

468
00:38:25,920 --> 00:38:28,000
But when Ms. Darin
came to invite us herself,

469
00:38:28,080 --> 00:38:29,520
it made me think.

470
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:33,280
If we don't have knowledge, no matter
how much we borrow, it'll be gone again.

471
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:36,440
Thank you.
Thank you, everyone, for coming.

472
00:38:37,480 --> 00:38:38,720
-Please, come in.
-This way.

473
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:39,640
Please come in.

474
00:38:39,720 --> 00:38:40,560
Yes.

475
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:41,920
Please sign in.

476
00:38:43,800 --> 00:38:45,320
Two lines, please.

477
00:38:47,160 --> 00:38:48,120
Thank you, Da.

478
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:54,480
Please go inside.

479
00:38:55,160 --> 00:38:56,960
-Next, please.
-Mr. Trai.

480
00:38:57,480 --> 00:39:00,360
The speaker called and said he can't come
and wants to cancel today's session.

481
00:39:08,720 --> 00:39:12,200
Not having a speaker means the event
will fail before it even starts.

482
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:15,040
How sad.

483
00:39:16,600 --> 00:39:18,840
Transfer the money to that speaker too.

484
00:39:20,080 --> 00:39:22,240
He suddenly had urgent business for us.

485
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:25,120
Yes, Mrs. Mookmanee. Uh, Mrs. Mookmanee…

486
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:35,920
Hello, everyone.
I'm Trai Bowornmongkolphong.

487
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:38,320
Thank you for taking the time
to be here today.

488
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:39,240
BORROW SMART SEMINAR

489
00:39:39,320 --> 00:39:42,000
Actually, today, I want everyone to learn

490
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:44,760
about how to manage and spend money.

491
00:39:45,720 --> 00:39:48,760
Looks like Mr. Trai
took over the speaker role himself.

492
00:39:51,520 --> 00:39:52,840
Trai?

493
00:39:54,400 --> 00:39:56,360
If you want to know
how to solve this problem,

494
00:39:57,280 --> 00:39:59,280
please welcome Dr. Wittaya,

495
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:02,480
a financial
and investment management expert,

496
00:40:03,240 --> 00:40:04,520
here to advise us today.

497
00:40:04,600 --> 00:40:05,560
Please welcome him.

498
00:40:13,200 --> 00:40:14,840
-Thank you for coming.
-Yes.

499
00:40:14,920 --> 00:40:18,520
BORROW SMART SEMINAR

500
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:20,280
Hello, everyone.

501
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:24,360
Today we're at the seminar
"Borrow Smart," right?

502
00:40:25,120 --> 00:40:26,200
What is this program?

503
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:28,320
Say you borrow 100,000 baht.

504
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:29,480
Who could know

505
00:40:29,560 --> 00:40:31,880
-what dirty tricks they could pull?
-You use 50% of it for the space…

506
00:40:31,960 --> 00:40:33,400
-I had to prepare, just in case.
-…to sell coffee.

507
00:40:34,160 --> 00:40:36,520
You use another 30%
to buy equipment to sell coffee.

508
00:40:37,120 --> 00:40:40,600
The last 20%, you keep
as working capital for the shop.

509
00:40:40,680 --> 00:40:42,000
In just a few minutes,

510
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:44,880
their applicant numbers
jumped into the thousands?

511
00:40:46,640 --> 00:40:49,360
The new speaker
is an investment guru, ma'am,

512
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:51,000
so his fans are in attendance too.

513
00:40:55,520 --> 00:40:57,400
If they're successful today,

514
00:40:59,320 --> 00:41:02,080
Trai's applicant numbers
will catch up to us.

515
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:04,120
I need to keep a wide lead.

516
00:41:10,520 --> 00:41:12,400
We have our people in there, right?

517
00:41:13,200 --> 00:41:14,240
Yes, ma'am.

518
00:41:15,040 --> 00:41:18,840
Then help make it so my competitor
can't keep running.

519
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:23,360
Yes, ma'am.

520
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:30,480
Eat, pay, shop!

521
00:41:30,560 --> 00:41:34,320
One app for everything. Be Rich!

522
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:39,120
That's right.

523
00:41:39,200 --> 00:41:42,360
You just have
to download the Be Rich app,

524
00:41:42,440 --> 00:41:45,920
and you'll get a chance
to win tons of prizes.

525
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:48,280
-We have motorcycles!
-Motorcycles!

526
00:41:48,360 --> 00:41:50,520
-Tablets!
-Tablets!

527
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:53,480
-Smartphones!
-Smartphones!

528
00:41:53,560 --> 00:41:55,960
-Gold!
-Gold!

529
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:59,960
The total prize value
is over 1 million baht!

530
00:42:04,160 --> 00:42:07,720
If you're interested, download the app
on your phone right now.

531
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:11,160
When the event starts,
we'll have lucky draws

532
00:42:11,240 --> 00:42:13,160
and prize giveaways.

533
00:42:13,240 --> 00:42:15,360
Yeah!

534
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:18,040
-You can register inside, please.
-Please come in.

535
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:19,360
-Please.
-This way, please.

536
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:21,840
-This way, please.
-This way, please.

537
00:42:21,920 --> 00:42:24,520
Hello. Have you downloaded the app yet?

538
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:25,320
-Not yet.
-No.

539
00:42:25,400 --> 00:42:28,640
If you haven't, hurry and download it now.

540
00:42:29,840 --> 00:42:32,320
We're about to start the drawing
and prize giveaway.

541
00:42:32,400 --> 00:42:33,960
Please come inside.

542
00:42:34,040 --> 00:42:35,680
This way, please.

543
00:42:53,720 --> 00:42:56,200
This loan features
an effective interest rate calculation.

544
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:59,400
You can borrow multiple times
within the designated limit.

545
00:43:00,360 --> 00:43:02,120
The bank won't force you or anything.

546
00:43:05,640 --> 00:43:06,760
Mr. Trai.

547
00:43:20,560 --> 00:43:22,160
Where is Trai going?

548
00:43:24,760 --> 00:43:26,600
You went to a hotel
with Rachen last night?

549
00:43:27,760 --> 00:43:29,640
If it's about that,

550
00:43:29,720 --> 00:43:32,200
let me call Mr. Rachen to clear it up.

551
00:43:34,480 --> 00:43:35,800
You have the same phone case as Rachen?

552
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:38,240
Rachen bought you a new phone?

553
00:43:39,560 --> 00:43:42,480
And who do you think stole my old phone?

554
00:43:42,560 --> 00:43:43,720
You're talking back to me?

555
00:43:47,760 --> 00:43:49,000
Are you just gonna stand there?

556
00:43:49,080 --> 00:43:52,080
She's bullying me.
Aren't you going to protect me?

557
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:56,360
-Uh…
-Or should I have my mom do it?

558
00:44:00,080 --> 00:44:02,680
If you did something wrong,
hurry and apologize to Ms. Mika.

559
00:44:04,560 --> 00:44:06,120
You obey her that much?

560
00:44:09,680 --> 00:44:11,960
Hurry up. Apologize.

561
00:44:12,040 --> 00:44:13,840
So Ms. Mika will show mercy.

562
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:15,560
Mercy?

563
00:44:17,440 --> 00:44:19,400
Bye. I don't want it.

564
00:44:19,480 --> 00:44:21,560
Then I'll have my mom fire Yongyut.

565
00:44:26,360 --> 00:44:28,240
Big mouth. Showing off.

566
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:30,640
You'll get us all screwed.

567
00:44:33,640 --> 00:44:36,600
Who do you think you are,
picking a fight with Ms. Mika?

568
00:44:37,960 --> 00:44:39,240
And you're still just staring?

569
00:44:39,320 --> 00:44:41,160
Give me your hands.

570
00:44:41,240 --> 00:44:43,080
Put them together. Kneel down. Kneel.

571
00:44:44,360 --> 00:44:45,680
Bow and apologize to Ms. Mika.

572
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:52,480
If I don't, what are you gonna do?

573
00:44:52,560 --> 00:44:54,640
Slap me like last time?

574
00:44:55,320 --> 00:44:57,920
So your precious Ms. Mika can feel better?

575
00:44:58,680 --> 00:45:01,320
Sounds good. I like that too.

576
00:45:02,160 --> 00:45:05,280
She's offering herself up, so do it.

577
00:45:06,360 --> 00:45:07,840
Make it so she can't talk anymore.

578
00:45:12,400 --> 00:45:15,080
Go on! Slap me.

579
00:45:16,400 --> 00:45:18,960
Pakbung, I'm trying to help you.

580
00:45:19,520 --> 00:45:20,920
Why are you forcing me to do it?

581
00:45:22,960 --> 00:45:26,680
Will you do it or not?
If you don't, I'll tell my mom.

582
00:45:29,000 --> 00:45:31,040
Go on. Slap me.

583
00:45:31,800 --> 00:45:33,240
Slap her.

584
00:45:35,080 --> 00:45:36,320
Slap me.

585
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:38,280
-Slap her.
-Slap me.

586
00:45:38,360 --> 00:45:40,800
Slap her. I said slap her.

587
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:43,800
Slap her!

588
00:45:57,000 --> 00:45:59,560
Don't cause chaos at my event.

589
00:46:10,800 --> 00:46:12,920
They managed to recover the files
from the hard drive.

590
00:46:14,440 --> 00:46:16,920
This is the suspect
who attacked you at the school.

591
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:19,280
Mr. Chan traced it
through this motorcycle.

592
00:46:24,440 --> 00:46:27,040
He destroyed the motorcycle,
so there wouldn't be any evidence.

593
00:46:41,120 --> 00:46:42,200
Wait.

594
00:46:42,280 --> 00:46:44,320
So we can see everything except his face?

595
00:46:44,400 --> 00:46:47,600
Yes. The technician said
he couldn't recover it 100%.

596
00:46:47,680 --> 00:46:49,760
But I didn't expect that part
to be unsalveagable.

597
00:46:50,400 --> 00:46:52,640
Someone died,
and we didn't learn anything new?

598
00:46:57,680 --> 00:46:58,520
Mr. Trai.

599
00:46:59,160 --> 00:47:02,720
You remember Ms. Kaew? The one Mr. Tritot
asked to check about the share purchases?

600
00:47:03,680 --> 00:47:04,720
Give me some good news.

601
00:47:07,080 --> 00:47:07,920
Here.

602
00:47:08,480 --> 00:47:11,240
Ms. Kaew followed the transfer trail
and found out

603
00:47:11,320 --> 00:47:14,800
who's using nominees
to buy up Be Rich shares.

604
00:47:17,200 --> 00:47:18,280
TRANSFER COMPLETE: 15 MILLION BAHT
MRS. MOOKMANEE

605
00:47:18,920 --> 00:47:19,920
Mrs. Mookmanee?

606
00:47:34,480 --> 00:47:35,320
Is there a fire?

607
00:47:35,400 --> 00:47:36,400
-Go, go!
-Run!

608
00:47:36,480 --> 00:47:37,360
Everyone.

609
00:47:37,440 --> 00:47:39,000
-Wait.
-Hurry!

610
00:47:39,080 --> 00:47:39,920
Calm down!

611
00:47:40,000 --> 00:47:42,280
-Everyone, please calm down.
-What happened?!

612
00:47:42,360 --> 00:47:43,240
Calm down.

613
00:47:43,320 --> 00:47:46,200
Don't panic. Please calm down.
Please gather here first.

614
00:47:46,280 --> 00:47:47,000
Is everything alright?

615
00:47:47,080 --> 00:47:48,320
-Da.
-Please keep calm. Trai.

616
00:47:48,400 --> 00:47:50,400
-Was there a fire? What happened?
-I don't know.

617
00:47:50,480 --> 00:47:51,760
Everyone, please stay calm.

618
00:47:51,840 --> 00:47:53,080
Follow my men.

619
00:47:53,160 --> 00:47:54,040
-Where?!
-Which way?

620
00:47:54,120 --> 00:47:55,400
-Calm down.
-This way, please.

621
00:47:55,480 --> 00:47:56,320
-Please stay calm.
-This way.

622
00:47:56,400 --> 00:47:57,960
-Calm down.
-Go, go!

623
00:47:58,040 --> 00:47:59,520
-Please stay calm.
-Go.

624
00:47:59,600 --> 00:48:01,000
-Let's go.
-Hurry.

625
00:48:01,080 --> 00:48:02,040
Please calm down.

626
00:48:02,800 --> 00:48:03,640
Everyone.

627
00:48:05,640 --> 00:48:06,640
Why is he going in there?

628
00:48:10,040 --> 00:48:11,280
-Where's Trai?
-Uh…

629
00:48:12,440 --> 00:48:14,200
I think you should go downstairs.
I'll go after him.

630
00:48:14,880 --> 00:48:15,880
Take care of her.

631
00:48:17,200 --> 00:48:18,400
This way, please.

632
00:48:28,400 --> 00:48:29,800
Who uses an elevator during a fire?

633
00:48:36,120 --> 00:48:37,160
Nothing.

634
00:48:41,920 --> 00:48:43,280
Stay still!

635
00:48:43,960 --> 00:48:44,920
Who sent you?

636
00:48:45,520 --> 00:48:46,320
Let me go!

637
00:48:46,400 --> 00:48:47,680
Stay still!

638
00:48:48,800 --> 00:48:50,560
Let go, Rachen.

639
00:48:51,200 --> 00:48:52,960
-Rachen.
-Mika.

640
00:48:53,040 --> 00:48:56,000
Today's event is very important.
I don't want any problems.

641
00:48:56,640 --> 00:48:59,640
A father and daughter fighting each other
has nothing to do with me.

642
00:48:59,720 --> 00:49:01,680
I didn't do anything. It's not my fault.

643
00:49:03,120 --> 00:49:05,080
Is this how Mrs. Mookmanee taught you?

644
00:49:05,160 --> 00:49:08,000
Yes. And you know what?

645
00:49:08,720 --> 00:49:10,600
Last night, Mom slapped me.

646
00:49:11,520 --> 00:49:12,560
Mom slapped me

647
00:49:13,240 --> 00:49:16,400
because of her. So she deserved
her dad to slap her for me.

648
00:49:17,120 --> 00:49:18,760
And it won't end with just a slap.

649
00:49:18,840 --> 00:49:19,800
Mika!

650
00:49:22,680 --> 00:49:25,920
Mika, I understand you hate her,

651
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:27,520
but we're adults now.

652
00:49:27,600 --> 00:49:29,040
If there's something you don't like,

653
00:49:29,120 --> 00:49:31,040
you endure it and hold it in.

654
00:49:31,120 --> 00:49:32,560
But if you can't do that, then go home.

655
00:49:33,160 --> 00:49:34,520
So you're kicking me out?

656
00:49:34,600 --> 00:49:36,120
Let's talk later, okay?

657
00:49:37,280 --> 00:49:39,960
Rachen. Rachen.

658
00:49:41,640 --> 00:49:44,320
Rachen, don't walk away from me like this.

659
00:49:50,880 --> 00:49:53,880
Rachen! Rachen!

660
00:50:20,760 --> 00:50:21,920
The news is out, ma'am.

661
00:50:22,840 --> 00:50:26,320
"A fire broke out
at the 'Borrow Smart' seminar

662
00:50:26,400 --> 00:50:29,200
organized by Trai Bowornmongkolphong."

663
00:50:29,280 --> 00:50:30,640
"People fled in panic."

664
00:50:31,520 --> 00:50:34,200
"Was it just an accident, or was it
a bad omen that he won't make it?"

665
00:50:35,360 --> 00:50:38,480
I had them write the headline
exactly how you wanted.

666
00:50:39,560 --> 00:50:40,960
As for the CCTV,

667
00:50:41,040 --> 00:50:43,080
I've ordered it cleared
for the whole building.

668
00:50:44,880 --> 00:50:45,800
Good.

669
00:50:48,520 --> 00:50:49,480
But…

670
00:50:51,440 --> 00:50:52,680
I still

671
00:50:53,200 --> 00:50:55,200
can't reach our guy, ma'am.

672
00:50:55,960 --> 00:50:56,920
What do you mean?

673
00:50:57,480 --> 00:50:59,960
It means your guy got caught.

674
00:51:18,400 --> 00:51:21,480
If you're going to slap me,
do it anywhere.

675
00:51:21,560 --> 00:51:23,680
You don't have to drag me
to somewhere hidden.

676
00:51:24,640 --> 00:51:27,880
Oh, come on, Pakbung.
I didn't want to do that.

677
00:51:27,960 --> 00:51:30,040
It was you. Why did you provoke Ms. Mika?

678
00:51:31,080 --> 00:51:32,760
Maybe I just wanted to remind myself

679
00:51:33,280 --> 00:51:35,040
what kind of father you are.

680
00:51:35,920 --> 00:51:39,080
You can hurt your own daughter
because someone else tells you to.

681
00:51:39,840 --> 00:51:42,160
Wait. Pakbung.

682
00:51:42,240 --> 00:51:46,400
At first, I always wondered
why Mika loves playing dirty.

683
00:51:48,640 --> 00:51:50,360
Guess she learned it from her mother.

684
00:51:52,680 --> 00:51:55,080
And you standing here blocking me,
scolding me,

685
00:51:55,160 --> 00:51:58,200
did you learn those manners
from your father?

686
00:52:01,920 --> 00:52:03,800
Well, I'm kind of a black sheep.

687
00:52:04,400 --> 00:52:06,160
I'm not exactly like my dad or my brother.

688
00:52:06,880 --> 00:52:08,600
It's obvious you're a rude person.

689
00:52:11,400 --> 00:52:12,920
And you know what?

690
00:52:13,440 --> 00:52:15,960
Your guy already confessed.

691
00:52:18,560 --> 00:52:21,960
He told me that you were the one
who ordered him to sabotage my event.

692
00:52:26,760 --> 00:52:27,760
My guy?

693
00:52:32,200 --> 00:52:33,400
Do we know each other?

694
00:52:34,480 --> 00:52:36,760
No, ma'am. I don't know you.

695
00:52:47,080 --> 00:52:48,920
Hey!

696
00:52:57,680 --> 00:52:58,520
What?

697
00:53:06,880 --> 00:53:09,200
If you don't know him,
then why does his phone

698
00:53:09,880 --> 00:53:12,600
have your secretary saved
as "Madam's Secretary"?

699
00:53:12,680 --> 00:53:15,960
There's even a message
from "Madam's Secretary" saying

700
00:53:16,960 --> 00:53:20,520
"Destroy the event"
at the exact time of my event.

701
00:53:21,400 --> 00:53:23,240
Your guy triggered the alarm

702
00:53:23,320 --> 00:53:25,760
and created smoke to fake a fire.

703
00:53:25,840 --> 00:53:27,720
That's why people panicked.

704
00:53:27,800 --> 00:53:30,920
Good thing we noticed it early,
or it could've spread to other areas.

705
00:53:35,240 --> 00:53:37,640
And there's a transfer slip
for 40,000 baht

706
00:53:37,720 --> 00:53:39,760
from your secretary to his account.

707
00:53:40,360 --> 00:53:42,160
You're still saying you don't know him?

708
00:53:44,400 --> 00:53:46,320
If you're so confident in your evidence,

709
00:53:47,120 --> 00:53:48,160
then file a police report.

710
00:53:48,240 --> 00:53:51,880
I did. The police are on their way.

711
00:53:57,600 --> 00:54:01,160
Then go ahead. Do whatever
you think will get rid of me.

712
00:54:02,960 --> 00:54:04,240
And let's see

713
00:54:05,160 --> 00:54:06,720
how this ends.

714
00:54:11,600 --> 00:54:14,640
But this time,
I didn't do anything wrong. It was you.

715
00:54:14,720 --> 00:54:17,120
You shouldn't have gotten
involved with Ms. Mika's man.

716
00:54:17,200 --> 00:54:20,840
Mr. Rachen is my employer. He pays me.

717
00:54:21,480 --> 00:54:23,360
If you don't want me
to be involved with him,

718
00:54:24,080 --> 00:54:25,200
then you pay me.

719
00:54:26,080 --> 00:54:29,120
Oh, come on, Pakbung. Everything
always comes back to money with you.

720
00:54:29,800 --> 00:54:31,880
Money's the most
important thing in life, right?

721
00:54:33,320 --> 00:54:36,680
It can buy anything, fatherhood,

722
00:54:37,360 --> 00:54:39,280
family…

723
00:54:40,120 --> 00:54:44,360
So important you can pay a father
to slap his own daughter.

724
00:54:46,760 --> 00:54:47,800
Okay.

725
00:54:48,720 --> 00:54:50,320
Okay, it's my fault.

726
00:54:50,920 --> 00:54:52,040
But Pakbung,

727
00:54:52,600 --> 00:54:55,280
just stay away from Mr. Rachen.

728
00:54:55,360 --> 00:54:56,640
Avoid him if you can.

729
00:54:56,720 --> 00:54:59,560
And stop provoking Ms. Mika, understand?

730
00:55:01,400 --> 00:55:02,800
Let me repeat this clearly.

731
00:55:03,720 --> 00:55:07,600
Only the person who pays me
has the right to order me around.

732
00:55:08,960 --> 00:55:10,840
You're the one
who taught me that yourself.

733
00:55:12,240 --> 00:55:15,360
You don't give me any money,
and you think you can tell me what to do?

734
00:55:15,440 --> 00:55:17,560
Ugh, Pakbung. Pakbung.

735
00:55:18,080 --> 00:55:21,080
Why don't you understand?
I'm not ordering you.

736
00:55:21,680 --> 00:55:25,440
I'm warning you.
I'm warning you because I care.

737
00:55:32,920 --> 00:55:34,880
You'll never get Be Rich.

738
00:55:36,320 --> 00:55:38,560
Even if you kill me
like you killed my dad,

739
00:55:39,800 --> 00:55:41,440
you'll never get Be Rich.

740
00:55:48,160 --> 00:55:49,800
Why would I kill you, Mr. Trai?

741
00:55:50,960 --> 00:55:52,520
This country has laws.

742
00:55:53,120 --> 00:55:54,600
If I were to attack you,

743
00:55:54,680 --> 00:55:57,000
wouldn't it be better
to hurt the people you love?

744
00:55:57,880 --> 00:55:59,240
It'd hurt even more.

745
00:56:05,880 --> 00:56:07,480
Who are you close to these days?

746
00:56:08,680 --> 00:56:10,080
Your father's wife…

747
00:56:11,240 --> 00:56:12,480
or…

748
00:56:14,440 --> 00:56:16,280
-that girl, Pakbung?
-Don't.

749
00:56:17,320 --> 00:56:19,000
Don't touch Pakbung.

750
00:56:20,880 --> 00:56:22,200
Mr. Trai,

751
00:56:24,720 --> 00:56:26,960
are you sure you want me as your enemy?

752
00:56:28,440 --> 00:56:31,960
Instead of picking fights with me,
you should go take care of your people.

753
00:56:33,440 --> 00:56:36,560
And I hope you can protect
your little Pakbung properly.

754
00:56:58,320 --> 00:56:59,160
Pakbung…

755
00:57:02,720 --> 00:57:06,520
Listen, Pakbung. Ms. Mika may be cruel,

756
00:57:07,280 --> 00:57:09,880
but she's not even half
as cruel as her mother.

757
00:57:09,960 --> 00:57:13,560
If Mika goes crying to her mom
and Mrs. Mook steps in,

758
00:57:14,160 --> 00:57:15,680
you could die.

759
00:57:23,280 --> 00:57:24,280
I know.

760
00:57:27,760 --> 00:57:30,600
I know I'm a bad father.
I can't protect you.

761
00:57:30,680 --> 00:57:32,440
But I really am worried about you.

762
00:57:34,560 --> 00:57:38,560
I'll say it again.
I really am worried about you.

763
00:57:44,080 --> 00:57:45,800
Yongyut. Yongyut.

764
00:57:50,640 --> 00:57:52,600
-I'm leaving now.
-Yes, Ms. Mika.

765
00:57:56,760 --> 00:57:58,040
Ms. Mika, watch out!

766
00:58:01,480 --> 00:58:02,880
Then give the plan back.

767
00:58:04,320 --> 00:58:05,880
-Whoa.
-Get down.

768
00:58:05,960 --> 00:58:08,480
And what do you need money for
when my heart

769
00:58:08,560 --> 00:58:09,400
is already in your hands?

770
00:58:11,480 --> 00:58:13,760
I'm giving you my body and my heart…

771
00:58:13,840 --> 00:58:15,840
Stop right now. That's enough.

772
00:58:16,440 --> 00:58:19,240
Please don't overlook my efforts again.

773
00:58:19,760 --> 00:58:21,400
Do you hug each other like this often?

774
00:58:21,480 --> 00:58:24,440
When you signed the contract with me,
didn't you read it?

775
00:58:24,520 --> 00:58:26,240
You're not allowed
to take jobs from my competitors.

776
00:58:26,320 --> 00:58:29,600
Pakbung isn't helping me as an employee.
She's here because…

777
00:58:29,680 --> 00:58:30,560
I need money.

778
00:58:30,640 --> 00:58:34,200
You think I'm going to make
Mr. Trai lose to Mr. Rachen, right?

779
00:58:34,280 --> 00:58:37,040
Because Trai's weakness is love.

780
00:58:37,800 --> 00:58:39,520
You are his weakness.

781
00:58:39,600 --> 00:58:41,640
Should I step away from you, Mr. Trai?

782
00:58:41,720 --> 00:58:43,520
Are you going to take everything from me?!

783
00:58:44,080 --> 00:58:45,040
You took things from me too!

784
